**Category:** essay-draft god-philosophers epistemic-subject faith husserl

**Abstract:**
A major philosophical essay titled "The Epistemic Subject and the God of Philosophers" arguing that the God discussed by philosophers is the correlate of a fictitious epistemic subject created by philosophers, not the God of faith. Analyzes Descartes' provisional moral code, Husserl's epoché, and distinguishes between spectator, witness, and participant modes of presence. Argues that philosophical phenomenalization of the world creates an ethereal epistemic subject incapable of encountering the God to whom one can pray and before whom one can dance (citing Heidegger).

**AI Recommendation:** Major essay central to Monasterio's critique of philosophical approaches to God's existence.

